<font color="#FF0000">GUILT?</font><br>
<tt>Wed Dec 24 17:54:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Landricks.<br><br>
No need to feel guilt. We all have a certain amount, I suppose.<br><br>
The war was so long ago, yet it is always there in my mind when I rise in the morning until I go to sleep at night.<br><br>
I have never had nightmares, so my sleep has been peaceful.<br><br>
Sure, I have had dreams about Vietnam. Usually they involve me having to go back. When I wake up, I never fail to have a sense of relief. Not guilt.<br><br>
The question shouldn't be: why was I spared? Rather, it should be: what am I doing with the life that I was allowed to live?<br><br>
The thing that is adundantly clear, when one is living and breathing, is that even if we have done little with our lives up 'til now, we always have tomorrow. It is never too late. Don't ever stop trying.<br><br>
Tom Dier <br><br>
C 1/52 198th Light Infantry Brigade Americal Division<br><br>

